D.q[6722] = "The alchemist and the Osamodas must be either side of a black flagstone. When they\'re in position, step on the black flagstone and we can go ahead and make the stone.";
D.q[1753] = "Iops are strong characters... sometimes nimble or intelligent too. They look for equipment that increases their strength and sometimes their agility or their intelligence.";
D.q[4445] = "What are you still doing here? Get out of here before we\'re spotted.";
D.q[6344] = "What more do you want to know? Are you waiting for me to do the work for you?";
D.q[5262] = "";
D.q[5670] = "What do you want from us?";
D.q[4457] = "Thank you! I\'ll pack my things right away!";
D.q[6062] = "";
D.q[7449] = "";
D.q[5549] = "HELLO! Can you give me a few Kamas please?";
D.q[5171] = "Me lie down... more shakey shakey.";
D.q[5760] = "Is Kaffra\'s mother around town? I remember her very well. \nI have a great idea for a present for her, but I\'m short of ribbon. Go find me 5 Linen Fibres.";
D.q[1728] = "Iops can use any weapon, but they handle swords and hammers best.";
D.q[3292] = "Irrrk!\nFnhiuh Chiiiii Krodosqueek doc krik kric?";
D.q[6367] = "Bwak bwak bwaaAAAK! (apparently you need to use the rope somewhere else).";
D.q[5972] = "You stay hewe with me. Me make you lots of Tiwabbits and you love me.";
D.q[6601] = "Hello noble servant of Bonta. Is the mission for the glory of Bonta advancing?";
D.q[1490] = "For a smart kid you can be real dumb sometimes. Ok, you need dentures just like the ones Elite Chafers have. You can try to take a set off one of them, but they\'re very well fixed on their skulls. You can also unearth a chafer\'s skull, which is easier to obtain, and ask a smith to melt gold onto it.";
D.q[2976] = "H\'lo stranger... Mmh... I\'m in the middle of a telepathic communication with the Magus Ax... I must tell him to stop, it gives me a bloody headache every time! Anyway! You\'ve been fooled! And let me tell you that this is serious! I recognize here the method of the Pandawa rebels called Pandikaze. They act on Pandala island and they\'ve sworn to ruin every adventurer looking for the Dofus. This one didn\'t miss you! If you\'d have had a Dofawa, I\'d have jailed you. You wouldn\'t be the first one to rot there!";
D.q[7509] = "";
D.q[6310] = "Stop right there! *Hic!* Only officers can go in the warehouse.";
D.q[4458] = "Can we leave now? If things get nasty I\'ll make sure to come back here. Having said that, it might be better if no one sees us leaving the library at the same time. You go first and wait for me outside, I\'ll join you just afterwards.";
D.q[6072] = "";
D.q[4505] = "Apparently you need a helping hand. I can\'t do anything for you, but I think I might have the solution to your problem. \nI\'ve a friend who could take care of it. But he\'s a strange person, and has a tendency to get paranoid. Very paranoid. \nHe\'s hiding out in Brouce Boulgoure\'s cave at the clearing, but I can\'t go visit him as a very unusual beast called Bellus Sel has blocked the entrance. That should sort out Nara\'s problem too, and you know how he hates problems.";
D.q[3291] = "Before becoming captain, cook, handyman, creator, singer, and cha-cha-cha dancer, I used to be a doctor.\nA doctor in spite of myself, but still a doctor.\nI\'ll try to put your bones together again, keep on concentrating...\nHow weird! Your heart\'s on the left and your liver\'s on the right.... It\'s supposed to be the other way around... Hum... Ouch... Here you go! I put everything I could back in place... Now you should be able to lie down in a click without your bones cracking! You\'ll be able to enjoy white sand beaches and my true stories.\nBy the way, Did I tell you that I once built Imp Transportations? And I\'ve also been the Imp chief after being captured by the Kanniballs from Moon Island, right before...\nHey! Come back! Why are you running away? Come Back! I haven\'t finished my story yet!";
D.q[5696] = "Why are you rummaging in your bag? Have you lost something?";
D.q[5612] = "Phew. A little good liquor for Terra Cogita to be drinkin\'.";
D.q[2876] = "You passed the ordeal, adventurer! The Forest awaits you!";
D.q[5655] = "Greetings. I\'ve been told that you had a few setbacks while interrogating Terra Bitya.";
D.q[6086] = "I didn\'t think the other Protectors expected so much of me. I must have been in retirement for too long.";
D.q[4479] = "Get out of my cave, or I\'ll smash your head in with a hammer! Assassin!";
D.q[2923] = "Greetings, my young follower. Seeing your resplendent face warms my heart. \nHow can I be of assistance?";
D.q[3328] = "Is Sadida preventing you from picking up flowers... or are you just lazy?";
D.q[4531] = "If I had this document, I\'d have even more influence in this city.";
D.q[6582] = "If only our militia had more warriors like yourself... You\'ve done well. I\'ll make sure to talk to Amayiro about you.";
D.q[2875] = "You can deposit both Kamas and items in your bank account.\nYou can only have one bank account. \nEvery time you access your bank account, even if you\'re just having a look inside, you must pay a fee.\nThis fee depends on the number of items stored in your bank account, and the number of items you can store in your bank account is determined by how long you\'ve banked with us. Each person living in the province of Amakna gets a bank account.\n\nSo, as time passes by, it will cost you more and more to access your account, as you deposit more items in it. However, the longer you stay with us, the more items you\'ll be able to put in it.";
D.q[6232] = "If you save me, I\'ll show you where the goblins left the Sram.";
D.q[5973] = "You love me. You stay with me and we make lots of Tiwabbits.";
D.q[5091] = "";
D.q[4642] = "Undress to your underpants. I want to be sure you\'re not hiding a weapon of mass destruction in there.";
D.q[6005] = "";
D.q[4443] = "Take the poison to the Spy Leader, in Bonta. He\'s hiding away in a corner in the South-West of the city.";
D.q[6012] = "";
D.q[5027] = "";
D.q[4424] = "A great victory. The Bontarian militia is ill-equipped. Now is the time to attack, but I want Kaffra Keeper\'s opinion before we do. If you don\'t know him already, you can usually find him in the Tower of Orders in Brakmar.";
D.q[6016] = "";
D.q[7356] = "";
D.q[2191] = "Is it my beloved Secsinbol who sent you? All right I\'ll do it for free, but only this once! I hope it\'s good wood, is it?";
D.q[6017] = "";
D.q[4020] = "Idiot! You have been unmasked! Leave me before I lose my temper!";
D.q[6018] = "";
D.q[3034] = "I must remember to have my shoes reshod the next time I\'m in town.";
D.q[4496] = "Did you find whoever\'s supplying us with weapons and check out their smith?";
D.q[6022] = "";
D.q[3596] = "Is it my boss sending you? He\'s a bit stressed out but nice. What can I do for you?";
D.q[1891] = "Is that for me? Even though I work in a flower shop, I think that\'s very sweet. Thank you.";
D.q[6028] = "";
D.q[5384] = "Is that your final answer?";
D.q[6043] = "";
D.q[1585] = "Isik ir piwik inik sivik tis Tibik!";
D.q[5746] = "It can cost you anything from 500 to 256,000 Kamas to go neutral. It all depends on how high you\'ve climbed in the ranks of your militia.\nWhat I can do is convert you to the weaker alignment for free. If you\'re a glory hunter looking to hop on the dominant alignment\'s bandwagon, well you\'ll just have to put your hand in your pocket!";
D.q[3007] = "It costs 69 Kamas.";
D.q[5039] = "Hahahaha... What a twisted sense of humour. A ridiculous symbol to fool your enemies and hide our true power! Very very good... here, take this for all your good work. I can\'t eat them, so what good are they to me?";
D.q[5699] = "Do you get a kick out of destroying all these valuable things right under my nose? You have no respect.";
D.q[750] = "The militiaman Atall Tramston was captured at midday while he was on reconnaissance near Brakmar. You must go to the Militia quarters to set him free.";
D.q[5040] = "WHAT! A TOFU CHARM??!!! HOW DARE YOU!!!";
D.q[5493] = "Hello, I\'m delighted to see you.\nI need resourceful gentlemen like you to help me with my work. I\'ve an easy, well paid task to offer you, but you must be discreet and not ask questions.\nWhat do you say?";
D.q[6496] = "Here you come with your airs and graces, expecting to carry on any old way you want. If you think I\'m going to hand over the information just like that, you\'ve got another think coming.";
D.q[391] = "It doesn\'t work if you know the ingredients in beforehand. You have to find them by yourself. Anyway I\'ve to admit that I don\'t have the list.";
D.q[2647] = "You must convince Master Dento to break engagement? Poochan not care how you do, but you do it very quick. ";
D.q[3279] = "It looks like you\'ve been bitten by a Treechnid... I think you\'ll have to undergo the terrible curse of this forest. I\'m afraid you\'ll start mutating any minute now... You should hurry up and get out of this dungeon while you still can. The exit lies right in front of you.";
D.q[593] = "Well, it looks as though you\'ve found everything I need to build my raft!";
D.q[3149] = "It took you a while to find these boomerangs! I\'ve been disarmed since you left! It was not the same! As promised, I\'ll reward you by teaching you one of my favourite spells. With this spell, you\'ll be able to throw magic boomerangs. Well, I don\'t expect you to be intelligent enough to understand all this, I guess that all this is beyond you. Listen carefully to what I teach you and then just get out of here! Lenald impaler!";
D.q[365] = "It\'s a family secret. All I can say is that I\'m short of some ingredients. Find them for me and I\'ll give you a magic scroll. I need 60 units of Blue Jelly, 25 units of Strawberry Jelly and 20 units of Mint Jelly.";
D.q[1372] = "It was your only choice anyway. If you come visit Oto without the report, I\'m sure he... Let\'s not waste any more time! You must collect lava samples situated within about a 5-mile radius. Find little peaks coming out of the ground, they indicate the safest places.";
D.q[5078] = "Will I send you there now?";
D.q[6570] = "It\'s a pleasure doing business with you. There are three places I can think of that would suit Nara.\nThe first one is close by, in the Crackler Mountain mine. There\'s a lot of coming and going in there, not to mention the larva hunters who hang around. \nThe second is in the village of Amakna, under the main fountain. It\'s a nice place, but a little humid to be honest. \nThe third is in the Porco Mine, in the east of the Porcos\' Territory. It\'s in the middle of nowhere, and quite difficult to get to.";
D.q[6768] = "It\'s a pity you want to leave, I was getting used to your company. After all, you can stay here so long as you don\'t do anything wrong. You could tell me all about the World of Twelve while you\'re here too, I\'ve been away so long, so many things must have happened. Is it as beautiful as always outside? Are those Iops as dumb as before? And the Ecaflips, have they lost their softness? My problem with Ecaflips is that I\'m allergic to their fur, it makes me sneeze constantly, so I\'ve never really spoken to one for very long.";
D.q[2878] = "You passed the ordeal, adventurer! The Forest awaits you!";
D.q[6591] = "It\'s an infection. Why are the gods being so cruel?";
D.q[6357] = "It\'s been a while since The Panta Maria set anchor in the Port of Madrestam. If she\'s planning to unload her cargo, I\'ll have to know what it\'s and where it comes from first. If it\'s contraband on the other hand, you can bet that Red Sharkham knows all about it. He\'d better give me a good explanation if he doesn\'t want to end up in the local jail, or worse still, in the belly of a local shark!";
D.q[6746] = "It\'s been fairly quiet lately, but we\'re keeping a close eye on things.";
D.q[1682] = "It\'s easy, for 40 Kamas, you can watch and bet on a larva race. Four larvae are in competition, bet on one before the race begins and, if it comes out on top, you get the jackpot... 40 Trool Tokens!";
D.q[4628] = "What? You\'ve found a turtle who knows where the horn is but refuses to tell you? Tofu Brain! Iop Head!";
D.q[5130] = "Did Merlinmagus manage to make the Truth Serum?";
D.q[5065] = "It\'s fine, the interpreter arrived. But even so, I think we\'ll have a tough time understanding what the Wabbits are talking about.";
D.q[2981] = "It\'s hard to hear the whisper of the future between this old beer-skin and the crook looking for innocents to fleece... What do you want? Let me guess... You want to know your future!";
D.q[6769] = "It\'s funny you ask, I can actually send intruders away from here. Once I sent this Bwork who\'d lost his way back to Incarnam, and given the number of casualties, I don\'t think he was happy about it at all. Sadida forgot to give me the gift of clairvoyance you see, so sometimes intruders aren\'t teleported exactly where intended. The landscape causes me problems too, last week I sent someone into what I thought was a clearing in a forest, and they found themselves smack bang in the middle of a group of starving Trools. You can guess what happened next.";
D.q[5134] = "Huh? The Order of the Sharpened Spatula? That doesn\'t mean a thing. But I like it! Ok, you got it... I declare the Order of the Sharpened Spatula OPEN!! The chief of the order will be the oh-so-powerful As\'Ruoy\'Dnim.";
D.q[2338] = "These underpasses ain\'t safe. Tofus get sick in there... You shouldn\'t hang around, it\'s too dangerous for young folk like you. Plus, helmets must be worn at all times, especially if you don\'t got no insurance.";
D.q[5663] = "It\'s no use bothering me if you haven\'t managed to get your hands on the guardian of the Statuettes.";
D.q[2430] = "It\'s out of town... on a farm, somewhere North-East of here.";
D.q[5606] = "It\'s not that I don\'t want to help you, but I\'m about to retire, so... could you spare a little something in return for the information?";
D.q[3557] = "It\'s nothing too difficult, I assure you, just rid the region of these parasitic creatures and you\'ll be well rewarded. I wrote what you have to do in your questbook. Happy hunting!";
D.q[4171] = "It\'s perfect! Thanks to these improved items I\'ll be able to fly a lot faster riding on my Scaraleaf without exhausting it.";
D.q[1673] = "It\'s quite easy, there are two different challenges based on the same concept. Puppet Blops will lay down some funky moves, one after the other. When the sequence is over, you have to mimic it by pushing these Puppet Blops in the same pattern. In easy mode, the Blops keep the same basic sequence and just add one movement with each turn. In hard mode the sequence is new at each turn. Wanna try?";
D.q[3568] = "It\'s simple. A flag is a symbol. Well, it\'s like a symbol, but it\'s not... it\'s like a symbol made out of cloth. That\'s it. I need a symbol... made out of cloth, get it?";
D.q[355] = "It\'s somewhere around here, I know it! I\'ll find this bloody entrance... It\'s not far away, I can FEEL it...";
D.q[2613] = "You stupid. This power of springs Juice-Sane-Ki-Oak. Can turn Poochan into Bow Meow to find future husband. Poochan not find. You want help me?";
D.q[312] = "It\'s true, you\'re entirely right! This potion isn\'t any more effective than unbuttered bread! I\'m an idiot, I can\'t find good potions anymore!";
D.q[1255] = "It\'s very generous of you. While you\'re at it, give them these invitation cards. Needless to say they must have them before tomorrow.";
D.q[3529] = "You travel with a Goblin looking good to eat!";
D.q[144] = "It\'s very simple, I hide a die under a tankard of beer, I move the tankards all over the place and you must tell me in which tankard the die is hidden. If you find it, you\'ll double the money you staked.";
D.q[4412] = "I... it\'s... it\'s a secret. Oh darn, I suppose you know that already! No matter, I\'ll sort you out. No one will stop me getting this jewel. NO ONE!!!";
D.q[1127] = "Jingle jinglejongle jijingle Jinglingle.";
D.q[1308] = "Jingling Jangling! Jingling Jangling! Jing Jang! Jingling Jangling!";
D.q[6597] = "Iz a miracle! I can\'t smell a sing! You \'ave great, great powerz, I can\'t deny. I sought I was a powerful mage... I\'m nossing!\nWhat is left of ze doll who was once a powerful Bwork of the caverns? If you patched \'er up a little. Or a lot. Maybe drench \'er in the enchanted waters according to ze ancient Zadida rituel. Zen you should be able to get a bit of information out of him. When ze rituel is over you\'ll \'ave to wait a few days for ze effects to take \'old, so don\'t bozzer rushing it. If you want to patch up your doll, call up a Zadida, zey are very good at zis. I know one, Mascara, who is an expert at zis.";
D.q[2118] = "Thanks for this form. I hope he/she will be a good delivery boy (girl)";
D.q[7547] = "Jorbak\'s spirit will not show for a while. The biggest fortunes are the slowest to build. Have patience.";
D.q[6354] = "Judging by the whiff of sulphur, you must come from Brakmar, right? I really don\'t know how people live in such an atmosphere... I need fresh air, me... the crunchy sniff of a morning stream, the beating storms of the sea.";
D.q[577] = "Just a sec... Right then, it fits you. It was worth surviving that long. Good luck and tell me about your little journey when you come back... If you come back that is, teehee...";
D.q[6222] = "If you have a few Kamas too many, I\'d be delighted to make some clothes for you to replace those rags. It would be a real challenge to make a mess like you pretty, a real challenge to my skill as a tailor. As for the face, however, I\'m no plasterer.";
D.q[4520] = "Just in case you\'ve already forgotten, Norb\'s workshop is south of Amakna, near the Porcos\' Territory. And the mine Nara works in is actually within their territory.";
D.q[2444] = "Just like you, all the creatures down here are either resistant or sensitive to the four main elements: air, earth, fire and water. Learn the strengths and weaknesses of each (as well as yours!). The World of the Eleven will be safe for you. Or almost.";
D.q[3701] = "Just look at that city... spreading out before our eyes. It\'s beautiful, isn\'t it? One day, I\'ll leave myself. I\'ll go on a great adventure around the world, I\'ll drink a mimilk at the Astrub Inn. Or maybe in Bonta. OR BRAKMAR! Imagine!";
D.q[6360] = "Just think that I was going to go on the search for a fabulous magic horn guarded by the most abominable creatures in the whole of the World of Twelve. I was then planning to use the horn to open the lair of the terrible Giant Kralove who dwells on the north of Otomai Island, then, once I\'d slain the creature, I was going to take on the guardian of the kingdom of the dead so as to win back the souls of my departed companions. Finally I was planning on going back to the homestead... ahhh, back to Penelope my wife. \nWhere have I heard talk about this magical horn? At the Ripate Inn of course... I stayed in Sufokia for a while.";
D.q[5222] = "Kalfen is the patient type, so I don\'t think prison will have had much of a effect on him. But maybe I can pressure him to increase my hold on the city...";
D.q[4428] = "Just when I need Shush Tercesasti\'s spies, he doesn\'t have any available, so I\'m going to have to make do with you. It\'s time to prove how good you\'re at infiltration and burglary. You mission is simple: break into the Bontarian militia building, find the new standard militia equipment, get our smith, Mulic Bere, to examine it, and report back to me with his conclusions. Do you think you can manage that, or should I send you off peeling potatoes for the rest of your days?";
D.q[6247] = "Keep them for the moment. You\'ll need them for another mission.";
D.q[3968] = "Killed Wabbit? Oh, no for goblins, no for goblins!";
D.q[4301] = "Keep your stupid jokes for the inn. One more remark like that and I\'ll pull your tongue out so far that it\'ll wrap around the ramparts of Brakmar.";
D.q[5654] = "Keep your threats to yourself. As soon as I get my hands on a Kalyptus Stem I\'ll give you the beating of your life.\nNow instead of talking nonsense, go and fetch me the cook. I\'ve a thing or two to say to him about his food.";
D.q[2305] = "Keuf! Kof! Keuf! *belches in a weird way*";
D.q[2306] = "Keuf! Kof! Keuf! *belches weirdly *";
D.q[3967] = "Killed Wabbit? Oh, no for goblins, no for goblins!";
D.q[5135] = "Hmm, the Order of the Stinging Slap, huh? Not bad... not bad at all. Ok, no problem. I declare the Order of the Stinging Slap OPEN!! The chief of the order will be the oh-so-powerful As\'Ruoy\'Dnim.";
D.q[3055] = "King Allister\'s hungry. And he wants Dragoturkey steaks. He\'s fed up with Wabbit in tomato sauce.";
D.q[3970] = "Killed Wabbit? Oh, no for goblins, no for goblins!";
D.q[5506] = "Kimbo Burger! Tiwabbit in spicy sauce! Ouginak cheek! Mashed Cawwot!\nHo humm... can\'t you see I\'m working?";
D.q[3969] = "Killed Wabbit? Oh, no for goblins, no for goblins!";
D.q[5140] = "Did Merlinmagus explain what the problem may have been?";
D.q[561] = "All this for next to nothing! Yes dear guest, hardly anything to be precise. The journey only costs 1,000 Kamas. But to travel in the best conditions, we ask you to equip yourself with a helmet and a pair of directive wings. Come back again as soon as possible with these little things to quickly take advantage of our special offer as it won\'t last for ever... Plus, invite your friends, holidays are so much more funny and exciting with several people.";
D.q[7070] = "Krk Irk Verk Ak Lk Ak";
D.q[2304] = "Kof! Kof! Kof! *loud cough that echoes from deep down in his throat*";
D.q[5084] = "Ku\'Tan? Is he still in our world? What a coincidence. Is he ready to take up service again? I\'ll certainly have some work for him.";
D.q[5639] = "Last night, I came across a Gobball that had a broken leg. I healed it until it was able to make it back to my house on its own. Then my friends and I cooked him for dinner. That\'s what I call healing.";
D.q[3188] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the first room, or maybe in the second one, or was it in the fifth? or the sixth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[6156] = "Amazing! You\'ve succeeded where many before you have failed. One last challenge stands in front of you, and it won\'t be the least of your trials. I need you to bring me the soul of a Kralove. I\'ve been studying these creatures for a long time and I\'ve discovered that a special soul stone is needed to capture their souls - the creature\'s soul is as unique as the creature itself.";
D.q[6136] = "So what about those souls I asked you for?";
D.q[832] = "I\'m completely broke, so don\'t count on me to give you a mission...";
D.q[6158] = "I can see you don\'t know how to capture souls yet... You really need to learn the technique, I can help you if you want.";
D.q[3193] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the ninth room, or maybe in the tenth one, or was it in the thirteenth? or the fourteenth?... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[4618] = "I sense that you have a magic object in your possession. I sense you wish to show it to me.";
D.q[6419] = "Don\'t fear me, young adventurer! I can send you to the cemetery ... without taking your meaningless soul from this terrible and dangerous world! Rid the world of all the species living in and I\'ll send you where they all end up...";
D.q[5158] = "Hello my little Scaraleaf, Elviana Tirips has asked to see you. He must be around the Tower of Bonta, so you shouldn\'t have any trouble finding him.";
D.q[7507] = "";
D.q[2796] = "Hmmm, I can feel that your feet wish to tread the damned soil of the maze. Are you mad enough to even think you could hurt Dark Vlad?";
D.q[4370] = "So, how did it go?";
D.q[5375] = "";
D.q[7510] = "I\'ve scrolls for all characteristics and powers. How powerful do you want your scroll to be?";
D.q[3191] = "Last time I saw Lord Crow, he was hiding in the third room, or maybe in the fourth one, or was it in the seventh? or the eighth?.... Well, I don\'t remember.";
D.q[353] = "Goodgoddarn, I\'m to-waaahh-tally beat... I\'ve lost my prechiouss possessions... bloo-ahhh-dy oath.";
D.q[5380] = "";
D.q[4568] = "Hello, have you come to give me some good news?";
D.q[6216] = "Ever since I was a kid I was into watchmaking and that\'s exactly why I chose to worship the god Xelor. Now that I\'m better at my hobby, well... it\'s not longer a hobby. You\'ll have to come see one of my shows at the arena actually. I\'ll show you how to make a grown Bworker cry, it\'s very entertaining. I\'m actually talking with Moob Tsinhcetoryp about putting on a pyrotechnics show.";
D.q[1646] = "Come, come close... wealth is for those who dare.\nThe pot has now reached #1 Kamas!\n\n100 Kamas to take part, if the Gobball eats the apple, a new life will be yours!";
D.q[1192] = "You don\'t seem to be ready to join our ranks yet.\nFirst, you must train. Go see Amayiro in the Militia barracks. He will explain what to do.";
D.q[5382] = "";
D.q[5385] = "";
D.q[6013] = "You find my name funny? Well if I were you I would wipe that smile off my face.";
D.q[5494] = "Last yea\' we \'ad sooo many kids cummin\' inta this cave... no\' many came out agin though!!!\nWe said to ou\'selves... \'why don\' we chaaage peepo\'?\' Weer lookin\' for customehs, so it\'s free for now.\nWanna come in?";
D.q[6556] = "Latem Sa is far from incompetent, there must be some mistake. There\'s surely another explanation for the poor quality of our militia\'s equipment. I must thank you all the same for alerting me to the problem. I\'m going to take measures to fix this. Keep serving our city to the best of your ability and Jiva will reward you well.";
D.q[4748] = "Leave me be, child!";
D.q[1208] = "Leave me alone with my grief...";
D.q[2566] = "Learn this: I used to be a very powerful Lenald, the most powerful of all. I was the Dofus warden! And when the Wabbits invaded our island, I took the precious egg with me.";
D.q[2575] = "Lealn this: I used to be a vely powelful Lenald, the most powelful of all. I was the Dofus walden! And when the Wabbits invaded oul island, I took the plecious egg with me.";
D.q[3727] = "Legend says that when he battled against the demons, Iop threw his sword to the ground to even up the odds. First the demons laughed. Not for long. His steady gaze followed the terrified beasts as they fled. They escaped the battlefield with their worthless lives, and Iop was victorious without lifting a finger. He left his sword where it lay to inspire courage and determination in his followers and in all other pure souls who pass.";
D.q[5855] = "Ledrob sent me you? I hope you can keep a secret.";
D.q[5383] = "";
D.q[1130] = "Lend me 5 Kamas. I promise I\'ll pay you back.";
D.q[3263] = "Lesson n°1:\nYou know that someone like you shouldn\'t lie to someone like me, don\'t you? \nSo if you know where my little boy is, say it right now!";
D.q[5216] = "Hello there... you know one so young should not hurry so. You look like you have something on your mind. What is it?";
D.q[1644] = "Leonzi Trool laid his dream bare to us. The minute we heard his inspired plans, we understood that our destiny was to help him to make this fair reality. And we did it! ";
D.q[7519] = "You don\'t have enough Doploons to exchange.";
D.q[5442] = "";
D.q[2898] = "I must take care of the level passage of many others enthusiasts. Try coming back in three hours, at least!";
D.q[7521] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[2823] = "Let me guess, you\'re too shy to ask an active fighter to fight with you...? Don\'t move, I\'ll go find someone of your level to fight with you so that you can train.";
D.q[4841] = "*The judge questions everyone in the room, and then calls you to the witness stand to recount what happened*\nIs it possible that Gnirreh, present here today, stole the secret document and then hid it in Kit Dingaround\'s bag without his knowledge?";
D.q[5664] = "Let me guess. you aren\'t able to catch a soul with your bare hands, is it? Go see Divad and explain your situation. Tell him I sent you and that it\'s urgent.";
D.q[7523] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[3282] = "As I explained to you, before becoming Allister\'s cook, I used to sail on the most beautiful and gigantic boat of all oceans! See that of Nikos Monot? Well, mine was twelve times bigger than his. You\'re speechless, aren\'t you? \nUnfortunately, it was too big for the harbour of Amakna. It didn\'t even fit! Can you even imagine that? \nIt was so gigantic that it beached on this rocky inlet when I arrived on Moon Island. Yep! It was so big that it linked this rocky inlet to Moon Island!";
D.q[5218] = "I seem to have been betrayed from all sides. Oto Mustam, Domen... I guess you just can\'t trust anyone in Brakmar.";
D.q[6486] = "Let me have a look at that.\n...\nThis report has been forged. There\'s a stink off it that suggests some dodgy dealings and your name has been scribbled on top of someone else\'s. See, the old name begins with an X. Some \'Jellidice Jellies\' have been used to cover the name, take my word for it. Larry Poller will surely be able to tell you more about this.";
D.q[1001] = "Let me introduce myself. I\'m Leonzi Trool, brilliant visionary and humble apostle of Ecaflip. I use my modest means to help people enjoy themselves. Today, I\'ve created something that will revolutionize the world of entertainment. And I\'m proud of it. But there\'s still lots to do.";
D.q[1366] = "As I promised, here\'s your reward. I still can\'t understand how you won though...";
D.q[4971] = "";
D.q[7050] = "Very good, now which gem do you want?";
D.q[7051] = "Very good, now which gem do you want?";
D.q[7052] = "Very good, now which gem do you want?";
D.q[3289] = "I used this machine to do some time-travelling and confront Sponge Mob to steal his sponge.\nHere is the little story.\nDid I already tell you that I was the first one to land foot on Moon Island?\nThat was one small step for me, one gia...\nYou want to get in the sand dungeon? You should have told me before! I\'ve used up way too much saliva just for you...\nIf you have the key to this dungeon, I\'ll let you in straight away. I\'ll tell you all my stories once you\'ll get back eat some fish in my restaurant, the one at the bottom of the sea, under Sufokia.";
D.q[7526] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[5067] = "Hello, you\'ll never guess what happened to me. Someone tried to throw me in jail! \nI want you to bring this piece of Rasputin Cake to Magus Ax in Astrub so he can identify where the poison comes from.";
D.q[4341] = "Let me see your blade. \nIt\'s not a common weapon, and judging by the claw marks on the hilt, it must have belonged to an Ecaflip. I\'m an expert in all blades but the ones Ecaflips use... you should go and ask some of them. Here, take your sword back.";
D.q[2998] = "Let me see this rag! Can you believe this? The old fart signed these books with my name, making huuuuuge mistakes! He did it on purpose! He just wanted to discredit me in my readers\' eyes! B-but... I can\'t write on it: the book is protected by Herdegrize\'s magic. Bring me back a Purple Piwi Feather so I can get rid of this bewitchment!";
D.q[7527] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[1184] = "Let me tell you something my friend, becoming a fishmonger is not easy... no! It\'s not easy at all. Even if you can bear the slimy, sticky goop all day long... and EVEN if you can stand the horrible smell from sunrise to sunset, or even longer... well you still have to cut the damn heads of these nasty creatures... Do you really want to spend your life doing that?";
D.q[2491] = "Let me tell you, oho, my family is a brave lot! My three brothers guard the underpasses, my uncle Manganeze is helping the Pandas build their bridge... You know that\'s a rough job... there\'s all sorts of highwaymen and thieves over there! (she prays) Goooood EnutroOOOOooof, I beg you, watch over them...";
D.q[3119] = "Don\'t come any closer #1.\nYou\'re nothing but a miserable wanderer and your pathetic life will end right here!\nBut... How did you manage to get here? Did you actually defeat the other Koalaks?\nWell, in that case, you\'re welcome... I like foolhardy adventurers!\nMy mistresses asked me to guard the entrance of this cavern where the Koolich is locked up and only adventurers with a key are allowed to get in. Do you have a key?";
D.q[4533] = "Let me warn you before you get too carried away that you won\'t be able to get in just like that, not in your wildest dreams. Sadida has protected the inner entrance to stop anyone who doesn\'t respect his power from stealing the book. If I were you I\'d play it cool, you know, have a bit of respect for the will of the gods. I\'d probably go look for the magic horn of Sufokia.\n...\nBut since you seem determined, I\'ll show you where the way in is. Then you can let me get back to my siesta. \nAhhhhhhem....";
D.q[5427] = "I know you\'re not here to take over from me. So why are you here?";
D.q[2612] = "You future husband of me? No, no you. You too weak. You stink. And you ugly. You get out sight of Poochan.";
D.q[4282] = "Let me warn you, if you don\'t bring the information on Xephires soon, I\'ll have a Gobball lick every orifice in your body.";
D.q[5220] = "Greetings. I\'m sorry, but I have no time at the moment. Come back another time.";
D.q[5196] = "Let us pass, we\'ll bring that roguish Goblin all the way to Bonta.";
D.q[4118] = "Let\'s say that you can equip a perfect Gobball Belt on top of the belt you\'re wearing now... How many Mojeeto Corals could you carry in all your equipment without having to give up any of your items? You seem to be quite bad at mental arithmetic, so I\'m going to give you a hand and suggest 5 different answers. Choose the answer you believe to be closest to the truth. Be careful! There\'s a trick! Don\'t forget to divide the captain\'s age by the number of gold, and then by the air constant and add 12.";
D.q[2835] = "Let\'s see... It seems you\'ve begun training with brave Amayiro.\nIt might be time for you to choose an order and to specialise in a field to best serve the interests of Bonta!\n\nI\'m part of the Order of the Sharp Eye myself. If you wish to know more about the other orders, I recommend you visit the other floors of the tower...";
D.q[5570] = "Let\'s see what we can find out from it...\n...\n... ...\n\nOk, got it! There is a ritual for forcing a soul back into a body. We\'ll need 1 unit of Phoenix Blood, 15 units of Magical Cure and 1 Lear Amulet, which you can get on the bodies of Treechnees and Dark Treechnees. You know what to do. Go for it!";
D.q[5449] = "Only seasoned adventurers dare to go down there. You\'re still too weak to survive an encounter with the crocodyls. Come back and see me when you\'re feeling better.";
D.q[3501] = "You give II, III or IIII *shows his filthy fingers* Bwork beer, me give good yum yum.";
D.q[629] = "Let\'s see... Oh, you want to become an alchemist? Yes, I\'m a trainer. So listen to me carefully: a good alchemist must be able to read the intensity of magic essence in any object so that it can be used appropriately. Give every item you own a new dimension.";
D.q[1975] = "Let\'z do zomething zimple. I can\'t go near this Enutrof, zo you\'ll be ze one to go get my report back. If you could avoid talking about thiz problem to the mazter, I\'d really appreciate it.";
D.q[7534] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[6188] = "Listen carefully. I\'m not your tavern buddy, so if you\'re looking for a chat, go somewhere else.";
D.q[5532] = "Listen carefully. If you quit the Order you\'ll lose your rank and all the benefits that go with it. On top of that, if you decide to come back to us later on, you\'ll start from square one and you\'ll have to regain everything you threw away. We don\'t like quitters round here.\nWhen you quit an Order, you can join another one right away, but you won\'t be able to quit that one before one week.\nSo, do you still want to quit your Order?";
D.q[5049] = "Listen carefully. You\'re going to go to Amakna and warn that big lump they call Sergeant Graccia that no action should be taken against Bonta. Have I made myself understood?\nBefore you leave, go see Ebru of El, he asked to see you immediately.";
D.q[5117] = "I\'m a captain in the Brakmar militia. To be perfectly honest, I\'ve been thinking about leaving soon. I\'m sick of never getting promoted after all these long days of loyal service.";
D.q[3551] = "You give me gob skin! Me use it to do tapestry work in hut of me.";
D.q[4554] = "Ah, that\'s horrible. Get that handkerchief away from me, there\'s no way I\'m touching that filthy thing. It\'s bad enough to look at, but the smell... as though it\'s been used to whip... unruly slave-fish or some such horror. \nListen to me carefully now, here\'s what you do: make a fire, and burn that godforsaken thing. Then heat water on the fire, and draw yourself a good, hot bath. Finally, and most importantly, chew on a hot coal for a while to get rid of that bad breath of yours.";
D.q[4377] = "Good choice. Here is the fake jewel. And don\'t tell anyone about any of this. We know where you live.";
D.q[2882] = "Listen to me carefully: I\'m going to explain to you how our arenas work. First, you must earn a special spell which will help you confront monsters in our beautiful arenas. You must have this spell if you wanna capture the soul of the creature you\'re after.\nThen, when you\'re equipped with this Rune, you must start a fight with the creature. If you use the power of the Rune during the fight you\'ll defeat the creature. The more powerful your Rune is, the easier it will be to capture the soul of the creature. You\'ll finally be able to confront the creature in an arena, either alone or with a group of other adventurers.";
D.q[5651] = "Listen to me when I\'m talking to you! I\'ve seen far stronger specimens than you. And don\'t think you\'re smarter than me just because you\'ve managed to lock me up in here.\nI\'m sure you\'re just another small fry who\'s hiding your inferiority complex behind a thorny veil of bad manners.";
D.q[7539] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[5653] = "Listen to me when I\'m talking to you... You\'re acting smart just because I\'m behind these bars, but it they weren\'t here to protect you, you\'d get a hell of a beating. I\'m sure you got your job with your daddy\'s connections. That what all the kids like you do these days.";
D.q[6461] = "Haha, you think I\'m just going to give it to you like that, do you? Were you born yesterday!? Hehehe.\nIt\'s 10,000 Kamas, not a penny less.";
D.q[5309] = "Has William Lenglad finally understood that he just has to stop raining on everyone\'s parade?";
D.q[2506] = "Long live Grandapan! *Gives a sharp look.*";
D.q[3846] = "You go first. I\'m going to stay here and take in this view.";
D.q[5911] = "Listen, this is the third time you\'ve come to ask for my help, so this time I\'m going to ask you a little favour in return. Have you heard of Morgan Faym\'n? She\'s a Iop disciple who took the place of the Newtroll Knight. She has agreed to send some Bontarians to our camp in return for some pots of wine, but that\'s not what I\'m looking for right now. Actually, ahem... well. I want you to find a present worthy of her charms... in the meantime I\'ll see what I can do for you.\nSo go talk to Oto Mustam, he\'ll know who exactly who the Bontarian turncoats in the Brakmarian militia are.";
D.q[3504] = "Lonely, I\'m feeling desperately lonely among bullies and bullies hunters.";
D.q[5776] = "Long, long ago, the sport of Gobbowl was dear to the hearts of the Amaknean people. It went like this - two teams of five took each other on and tried to fire as many Gobballs as they could into the opposing team\'s cages. \nEverything was rosy till the society for the prevention of cruelty to Gobballs started sticking their noses in our business. These days, we usually pick one player to stand in for the woolly devils, but some players still prefer to use summoned Gobballs.";
D.q[3650] = "Look at me... talking and talking and I didn\'t even ask what you were here for!";
D.q[6505] = "We captured a Brakmarian who was trying to escape. He\'s being brought to prison right now.";
D.q[7543] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[2879] = "May a thousand roses bloom under your feet, perfume your toes with a soft Spring smell and make the nice season hurry!. That\'s how Grandapan talks, the wise man who reigns Pandala island.\nIf you agree with him and think spring is slow to arrive, it means it\'s time for you to move along! Hurry up! On Pandala, a whole lot of pure-hearted, fresh-breathed heroes are already fighting blood-thirsty monsters, just enough to keep them at bay in fact. Even better: when you go to Pandala, you might get to know the truth about those dragon eggs called Dofus! You still here?";
D.q[3619] = "You in Bworkcine\'s den? You clean feet before enter?";
D.q[583] = "*Hic* I can giive youuu a piece of the *hic* sail of my fooormer boat. It\'s the onlyy *hic* thing I haaavve leeeftt. I\'ll exchange it for 10 Kokonuuuts. *hic*";
D.q[1994] = "... \n*It looks like this girl is sound asleep. Yol gives you a nasty look as you stare at her*";
D.q[3631] = "You kill Piwis for Gobrator.";
D.q[4029] = "A Wabbit transformation formula! Show me this parchment ... staff, ahem ... cawwots ... hemp, yes ... Oh! I see! Wabbit teeth are missing! I\'m not surprised that my colleagues didn\'t know. I\'m the only alchemist specialised in bones in Amakna!";
D.q[5611] = "Look at that, the old Bworks wantin\' to capture old Terra Cogita, roast him up like a porker, but no, he had more sense. They fed Terra for years they did, though they did. But he was puttin\' the food in his beard the whole time, and the birds came down and eat the lot! Bworks don\'t be thinkin\' much.";
D.q[6301] = "What\'s this, an evil fiend has paid me a visit... You\'re looking for a Potion of Anguish? Or is it some nightmarish incense you seek?";
D.q[6439] = "Look now, a strapping warrior like you shouldn\'t play shy. If you do business with me, I\'ll soon lighten your purse. That will take some of the weight off your shoulders. Purses are like cups, you must empty them to fill them up anew.";
D.q[3540] = "Look who\'s coming... a Iop warrior! Ah yes, the glory-hunters... everyone wants to be a Iop! All the same, I\'m in need of a close combat expert.";
D.q[6740] = "Look, it\'s no secret. The quickest way to get rich is to bring in millions of Kamas, am I wrong? You want to know HOW to do this? Come a little closer, we don\'t want everyone to hear, do we. \nOk, to earn big bucks, you just have to not tell anyone where you\'re getting your money from. \nGood advice, huh?";
D.q[2180] = "Argh, that\'s what I was afraid of... even my skills have their limits. But Ma Cleopatra\'s talent is as unwavering as Djaul\'s stench-ridden breath. I told her about it, and I think she\'ll be able to help Locette, go and talk to her, quickly!";
D.q[5328] = "Ah, there you are. Ronan has been acting very strange since he lost the battle against Bonta\'s defenders. I tried to reason with him, but to no avail. Maybe you would have more luck?";
D.q[2716] = "Looking for a Dofus, are you? These eggs bring violence and desolation wherever they lie... In Pandala, people seem to talk a lot about them lately... But I\'ve my own little idea about it - these eggs are harmless! The only thing which should be exterminated is your group of greedy adventurers! Then we shall be at peace again...";
D.q[5329] = "Ehhhh, Mwaaa blop... mwaaa blop";
D.q[2232] = "Hmm, cake? Oh right, the one I was waiting for earlier? I ran out of patience and started work on a new sword. Put take cake over there somewhere. Thanks for coming over by the way!";
D.q[5332] = "Me not dead? Me have skin, me have bones... me not Chafer... me Ooogi... Ouginiii... Ouginahhhh...";
D.q[2685] = "Looking to quench your thirst? Stop looking! You found your woman! I\'m the Pandawa you need! What can I do for you?";
D.q[3169] = "Lord Crow is on the map 9719.";
D.q[3014] = "Lucky you.... I still have a few copies left! This book is selling well at the moment! Herdegrize should give me more copies.";
D.q[1111] = "Lots of people mistake me for a girl... *sob* and when they realize I\'m a boy they call me every name under the sun *sob*. But I remember them all and one day, *sniff* I\'ll take my revenge! heh heh heh!";
D.q[3168] = "Lord Crow is on the map 9721.";
D.q[3798] = "What\'s this? A little slug crawling up to talk to me? ME! Bah! I don\'t have time for this loser.";
D.q[5417] = "Hello, what wind of fortune blows you to my door?";
D.q[354] = "Hello my friend! I\'ve got the best scrolls in all Amakna!\n\nJust prove you\'ve killed 100 Blue Larvae by bringing me their skins and I\'ll give you a Small Strength Scroll.\nI can do better, though! For 5 diamonds, I\'ll give you a Spell Point Scroll.\nWell, you know what you have to do!";
D.q[4410] = "Go and post militiaman at each exit of the Tower of Orders, I don\'t want those devils to get away from us. We need to catch them in the act, and I\'m counting on you to get it done. I\'m going to send one of my spies to follow you, just in case things get ugly. And don\'t take just any militiaman. I want you remove the following soldiers from their current duties - Sen Eiser, Kit Dingaround, Galde Avout, Ruth Banke.";
D.q[4712] = "Kit Dingaround? Sure he\'s come to see me. He ordered a new sword off me.";
D.q[604] = "A solid helmet? And what for? During fights only an impressive helmet could change the course of the fight, besides the weapon of course. Only miners need to wear a \'solid\' helmet, pfff!";
D.q[2507] = "Interesting! Your eyeball is REALLY wan... Let me guess: first, your breath smells like a constipated Dragoturkey... Then, your last meal is trying to escape your body through every possible hole. And finally, you\'re wearing a Pandawa hat in Pandala without being a Pandawa from Pandala! No doubt possible... you\'ve been McSheth\'d!!!";
D.q[3374] = "What, what! My child, you shouldn\'t just turnip unannounced. Hahaha! Ah yes, you have done well young one. Ha!... but it\'s not over yet. Here is the key that will lead you to your next challenge.";
D.q[4257] = "I\'ll need a very good shaft to fix your weapon. Bring me a Lady Root together with your cursed sword, and I\'ll fix it. ";
D.q[4393] = "Do you have the venom? The last three assassinations I did really ate into my supplies.";
D.q[5426] = "";
D.q[5522] = "Ahh no, this won\'t do at all. Your last conversion was less than two weeks ago. The Amaknan social services won\'t even consider your request if you\'ve put in for a change less than 14 days before. \nBe patient. And come back when the time is right.";
D.q[1966] = "Ahhhh, money, thank you very much ha ha. I\'m the chief, what can I do for you";
D.q[2342] = "Ahhh! There\'s no end to this harvest. Luckily for us peasants, this year\'s crop is gonna be a bumper!";
D.q[2902] = "All right, last question : \nIf you give an Evil Dandelion to a Wabbit, will it make it more intelligent, more lucky, or more agile?";
D.q[2416] = "Hi, I\'m just a young apprentice... If you want to know more about our art, go and see Enileda. She\'s been spending a lot of time in the marketplace since it opened not so long ago.";
D.q[2424] = "Although hunting is the most difficult of the harvesting professions, it\'s undoubtedly the most exciting. The hunter\'s raw material is found on the beasts that roam the forests of the world - on their bones that is! For many hunters, work and pleasure are one and the same. The greatest among these thrill-seeking maniacs are even said to hunt dragons! That is one rumour I can\'t believe.";
D.q[2627] = "And even, I can feel he\'ll find real happiness with someone like you... 25,000 would do! Deal!";
D.q[3092] = "There\'s a shark ogling me in the harbour. Each time I unload barrels from a ship, I\'m scared of falling into the water and being devoured. I\'d need something strong to help me forget.";
D.q[2791] = "Are you looking for the ultimate protection before entering the Damned Forest?";
D.q[1901] = "Argh! It\'s getting worse and worse, I couldn\'t go to the dates I had. So I decided to invite them all to the Trool Fair to make up for it... Now, I\'ve 3 dates at the same time. \nHow am I gonna do all this?";
D.q[2993] = "Aren\'t you done with your questioning yet?";
D.q[3173] = "Argh! Bullickish krass! Huh?";
D.q[2603] = "As stipulated in article 33 of Grandapan\'s Pandic Civil Code: it\'s strictly forbidden to sell Bamboo-based drinks to unauthorised persons. I\'m sorry!";
D.q[5073] = "What with the one that stinks of rotten snapper and the judge who stinks of alcohol, you\'d think we were at the Sufokia Fried Snapper Festival.";
D.q[2987] = "At the end of our conversation, I\'ll entrust you with a book in which everything will be explained.";
D.q[6747] = "We\'re taking a little break to catch our breath. Make the most of it and get some energy back, the bandits could attack at any time.";
D.q[3208] = "At last! Blimey, you took your time, didn\'t you? I doubt you even listened to a word I said! You\'re almost at the centre of the labyrinth now, though. What can I do for you?";
D.q[2892] = "Ouch! My bag is way too heavy! But I must say you can find everything you need in Pandala! It\'s WICKED!";
D.q[6425] = "Stolen goods? I\'ve never uttered a word about stolen goods. You must have heard wrong. I said \'swollen goods\'.";
D.q[3094] = "Ayaah!";
D.q[1865] = "Bahhhh, no... a little \'adventurer\' like you would never dare do such a thing to me... TO ME! Just go away, you little...";
D.q[3507] = "As you know, I\'m the greatest magus of all the Bworks. I feel terribly lonely here since I\'m the only one with a brain in this region...";
D.q[2808] = "Before you can even think of a gaining a new level, go read your handbook!";
D.q[2651] = "Because this art uses a lot of moves with the shield, beginners should have a light one - it doesn\'t need to be too solid. As for the Pandasiman masters, they can carry out their moves with heavy and very solid equipment. When you witness their mastery, even with a Feca shield, the fluid motion, the power... You\'ll understand my pride.";
D.q[4716] = "You\'ll also need some cursed iron for the blade. I\'ve heard something about it... our friend Mulic Bere the smith should know more about it.";
D.q[1595] = "Bhat bo you want buman ? How bo you bare to bisturb this bame?";
D.q[1922] = "Besides wood and ores, jewellers use loads of living and natural materials coming from some monsters living in the surroundings. These materials are used for working the substance itself or for extracting a magical essence/oil proper to spells. Speaking of which, I\'ll need some Arachnee legs... its essence gives a special shade - besides adding a little extra magic!";
D.q[3164] = "Bring me back the ingredients I need to finish my potion.";
D.q[2262] = "But what have you done? I\'m not interested in knowing you if you can\'t get what has to be done into your big loaf.. Take another leaf and look harder this time...";
D.q[5851] = "Hello, we\'re having some problems with the rationing of potatoes lately.";
D.q[2358] = "Can\'t you see I\'m a hunter? Go to hell!";
D.q[2688] = "By the pints of the goddess! You need a little tonic! I\'ve got what you need. What do you want to buy?";
D.q[5902] = "Greetings. How are you getting on with the Amaknan Militia? Is Bené Roisrond being cooperative?";
D.q[1317] = "I\'m Colonel Lyeno from the Bonta Militia. I\'m waiting for that dolt Amayiro to send someone to help me escape.";
D.q[5908] = "Greetings, have you been busy torturing as usual?";
D.q[6709] = "On the other hand, I\'ve to learn to count on myself, and nothing\'s protecting me from a bad harvest. Tell Raymon Santho that I\'ll meet him in three days at the Farmers\' Market.";
D.q[2600] = "Disciple, you still have a lot to learn about the Pandawas. What do you want to know?";
D.q[2860] = "You\'ll be able to go out in about 5 minutes. This jail is way too small for us to lodge such wretched beings as you all the time...";
D.q[2023] = "Do you plan on studying divination?! I doubt it... or I\'d already know!";
D.q[5595] = "That\'s wonderful! So all that we need for the spell Transgenesis is 20 Poppy Seeds? I\'ll take care of it.";
D.q[5927] = "Did you meet our goddess? Have you got the letter?";
D.q[2708] = "Do you really want your head to flavour a barrel of Pandneken? You have no choice anyway...";
D.q[5929] = "I\'ve prepared all the documents you\'ll need for your meeting with Maimane.";
D.q[2223] = "Don\'t forget to say your master I\'m taking care of \'is Tofus!";
D.q[3455] = "Don\'t you know me? I\'m Feldz. The greatest miner this side of Amakna! \nI\'ve been gogorified 7 times in the last two years and I\'m still here! \nI\'ve been miner of the month for 12 years running... once I won using my teeth alone!\nI\'m the pride of the Enutrofs\'! \nMy family has been living in these mines for 21 generations. The earth hides no secret from us!\nI dress up as a Dark Miner to go unnoticed, that way they leave me alone...";
D.q[2932] = "May the holy torrent inundate you with its kindness, may its power carry you away and its divine star guide your actions!";
D.q[2456] = "Eh, are you kidding me? Show me the wanted notice!";
D.q[5463] = "Ehhh, mine cousin tell you too?";
D.q[1722] = "Enutrofs can use any weapon, but they handle shovels and hammers best.";
D.q[1967] = "Ever heard of the Law of the Jungle? Well, this is the Law of the Fungle. Get it? Loofi, Delminss, kill him!";
D.q[2088] = "Ma Cleopatra has developed a cure... What a gifted healer, she gives a great foot massage too... but anyway! Find her and ask her if she can give you some Subosycold. Then, bring it to Clint Pot. He\'s an Enutrof, he will know how to care for our Tofus. Just follow your compass.";
D.q[7134] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[5944] = "Don\'t think that just because your in the militia you can sit back and take it easy.";
D.q[1793] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[4280] = "I think they looked like Goblins... or Bworks. Or Treechnids maybe.";
D.q[1829] = "Make sure you\'re ready before you go fighting a Dopple. So, are you all set?";
D.q[5946] = "Hello again. How are you getting along with your investigation?";
D.q[2143] = "Everything, everything EVERY BLOODY THING!!! The Fecas have to take care of everything! You\'d think we were the only ones with a brain...and please don\'t mention these lops... please! I feel stupid just bloody well thinking about the cretins.";
D.q[5948] = "Good day, loyal subject! Long live Allister, long live our great sovereign! May the king live a very long time.";
D.q[2727] = "Everyone says those paths are twisting and the creatures that haunt them are not what you\'d call friendly. But a fellow by the name of Wally Elconom succeeded in drawing a map. It could be useful for you to meet him. He\'s often to be seen round Amakna.";
D.q[3739] = "Farmers from Amakna usually make their mark in the fields of Cania before venturing further afield.";
D.q[4344] = "Hello, have you taken a trip round our beautiful city?";
D.q[609] = "For instance, look at those pink shorts. You wouldn\'t think they were anything special, would you? However, they\'re the magic shorts of the Captain of the Pirates... Some people say they bring luck when at sea. I\'m sure I\'ll sell them for a good price.";
D.q[2687] = "By the pints of the goddess! You look like you need a little tonic? I\'ve everything you need. What do you want to buy?";
D.q[2622] = "Garooph\n*He puts a ball on his muzzle and starts to dance.*";
D.q[6481] = "I don\'t have the authority to show you the report, so don\'t even bother trying to make me.";
D.q[3013] = "Go and see Elya Wood, in the Temple of the goddess Eniripsa. She\'s very smart and does not need this type of scroll!";
D.q[2145] = "You still look like a maggot to me! Get back to practice.";
D.q[1989] = "The remedy didn\'t work, I hope the doctor has another idea.";
D.q[4244] = "Good Evening!";
D.q[5571] = "Greetings. The rotting bodies of those imposters has started to bother the Jailers. Did you bring what we need to resurrect them?";
D.q[2778] = "HYAAAAAAAAAK HAHAHA! Meeting me, is like entering a world of pain... Bwahahahaha.... I\'ll let you speak, then I\'ll steal your soul!";
D.q[1096] = "H\'m, Tsog was a brilliant soldier, he died the death of a hero. The problem was the silly old fool wanted to be buried in the deserted cemetery east of Bonta...";
D.q[1553] = "Ha, there you\'re #1... so you received my letter.\nI need a rare ingredient for my next recipe. I need dust from creatures they call Onis. The beasts live right in the heart of the Evil Forest of Amakna.\nYou\'re the only one who can do this for me.";
D.q[3435] = "Hans and Gret, yeah, I think I\'ve seen them. They were playing with young Jorg Dy.";
D.q[5483] = "Apparently, the goblin\'s called Ronan and he has an unreasonable love for apples... But he doesn\'t seem to be dangerous.";
D.q[3898] = "A conspiracy! In the name of the Twelve, can you prove it?";
D.q[487] = "Heheheh, these secret missions are for clan masters only.";
D.q[4354] = "Ecaflip travellers? Nope, haven\'t had any in my tavern lately, no.";
D.q[3410] = "Many have seen the stalk from afar... few have munched on the turnip... do you understand?";
D.q[5960] = "Greetings. I\'ve been told that you\'ve found the way into the underground kingdon of the blessed Guenelous bénis Is it true?";
D.q[5773] = "Making you neutral is going to be no easy task. There\'s not a soul in all Amakna who hasn\'t heard of you. You\'ll have to shell out 256,000 Kamas to go neutral.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[6734] = "Make your request.";
D.q[6092] = "Many Protectors have no respect for one another, and this Assembly is only pulling them further apart. Nothing good can come of this.";
D.q[384] = "Hello there, my name is Heul Leise and this is my adopted son, Moor. I\'ve always dreamt of setting out on a big, exciting adventure. One day, I was all ready to go, but Moor started to cry, he held my arm and screamed Father! Heul Leise! Come back!\nThat\'s just how the little guy is. Oh, it broke my heart, so I decided to stay. \nSo, to make a long story short, I don\'t need my Great Scrolls of Strength anymore.\nI\'ll exchange them for something.";
D.q[5963] = "Dear Jiva is in good form today, she seems particularly lively.";
D.q[6781] = "I punch so hard that the air around my fist bursts into flames... it\'s simple physics, but you wouldn\'t understand. You wanna fight?";
D.q[5964] = "We have to fight harder than ever.";
D.q[4504] = "Don\'t you think if I wrote a letter to Norb he might come help us? No problem, I\'ll write a letter straight away. \nHere you go.";
D.q[3236] = "Hello! My name is Ziho. I guard the ruins of this temple. I know this village and this island like the back of my hand.\nI\'m used to meeting adventurers like you who don\'t believe the history of this place to be a serious matter... and never come back!   \nLet me help you with a little piece of advice. So, what do you need to know?";
D.q[1963] = "Good! Now you\'re going to find one of my agents, he must be somewhere close to these Enutrofs. He should have some highly important information for me. Just follow your compass, I\'ve shown you the way.";
D.q[5966] = "Things have taken a turn for the worse... something bad is on the way.";
D.q[2540] = "Hello! You\'re welcome to my house noble stlangel. You\'ve got an eye that sparkles like a stal in the night... and I see that she sent you by Flolarala\'s amulet... What can I do fol you?";
D.q[367] = "Hello, my name is Quincy Praïze. I make surprise-eggs with my father, Quin Praïze. But we need some ingredients. If you help us, you\'ll go away with a nice reward.";
D.q[624] = "Hello. As you can see, I\'m very busy at the moment. I\'m studying these spotted rocks. So please be quiet. I must concentrate.";
D.q[4051] = "Hello. I see you\'re a valiant warrior... Would you like to help us protect Amakna and Allister\'s throne?";
D.q[3732] = "Hello. What\'s an old spirit like you doing round all these young souls? What do you want?";
D.q[2215] = "Help! \'Ate my Sniffallrat Tofus! \'Wants our lives!";
D.q[973] = "Hem, sorry #1 but I\'m too tired to train today...";
D.q[5977] = "Gnnnn... gnnnnn... By my pipe, it won\'t come out... gnnnn...";
D.q[1700] = "Here is your prize, see you soon.";
D.q[2193] = "Here is the masterpiece... The string isn\'t too tight, but it\'s OK for a beginner. Now you just need to find someone who\'ll agree to teach you the art. My beloved Setsinbol would be perfect, but everybody knows that his daughter Ticra is the best.";
D.q[1624] = "Here you go. Happy fishing!";
D.q[6306] = "I could fast for three centuries and never feel even a touch peckish.";
D.q[1607] = "Here\'s your powder. See you later.";
D.q[2819] = "Here\'s the bridge to Astrub. Follow it and you\'ll find the Mercenary city.";
D.q[5788] = "Hey ho adventurer! Don\'t come too close, I\'m evil, me.";
D.q[3216] = "Hey there adventurer! How is it going? Do you want a Grawn? \nOh, fine then, don\'t answer! I don\'t care.\nWell, I\'m sure you\'re trying to get into this maze but I can tell you don\'t know much about it! You need a special key if you want to enter and don\'t count on me to just hand this one over. I usually steal them from adventurers like you.";
D.q[3545] = "Hey there young Osamodas! Did you come here alone? How strange! Usually your type wanders abroad with summoned creatures by their side. Well, it\'s not for me to decide, but I do advise you summon a companion for the task I ask of you.";
D.q[1310] = "Hey! Some cheques are missing! Are you trying to do me out of Kamas?";
D.q[5978] = "A Bontarian! What are you doing here? Tell me before I cut your throat.";
D.q[1082] = "Hey, just because an old lush doesn\'t see me that makes it an evidence to you? Don\'t make me laugh, of course I\'m having my breaks.";
D.q[2202] = "Hey, no problem... If I was you, I\'d go see Enileda. She can make you a nice bow and everything.";
D.q[1221] = "Hi there noble traveller, how may I be of help?";
D.q[1642] = "Hi, do you fancy a fabulously delicious sweetie? We\'ve got anything your tongue could dream of - fizzy ones, sticky ones, messy ones... The only ones we don\'t sell are multijellies, but you can\'t blame us for that, huh!?";
D.q[5983] = "Did you take the object and the instructions as I asked you?";
D.q[1093] = "Hm you\'re not the sharpest tool in the shed, are you. Take my badge for your registration.";
D.q[7106] = "You beat the Dopple? Congratulations! Here\'s your reward... you deserve it.";
D.q[1876] = "Hmmm, some parts came from my house, I\'m sure of it. But other bits look more like wood shavings. Hey look, there\'s a hair clip here... But... but it can\'t be... It\'s Marp\'s! MAAAARP?";
D.q[2665] = "Hmm, it doesn\'t surprise me you\'re from the future, you know. I get a visit from some time-traveller or another every other day! \nI must say, though, none of them have brought such ominous news... All this business about the demons of the hours is quite alarming...";
D.q[2395] = "Hmpf, I\'m a staff carver but above all, a master Lumberjack. No tree can resist the swippity-swipe of my axe, not even the great Elm. This job is rather easy so long as you have time. You just need to know the good spots.";
D.q[3366] = "Hoho! Insistent, aren\'t we! Well, prove you can fight, then. Find some creatures in the area and kill them... I\'ll prepare a series of challenges worthy of the greatest of warriors. Come back to me when you\'re ready!";
D.q[7055] = "It seems that you either don\'t have the level required or you don\'t have enough Strokens.";
D.q[3994] = "honour\'s in battle, not in slavery!";
D.q[2683] = "Hola! Do you like this sweet fermented bamboo perfume?! We\'ll get on well then... What do you want?";
D.q[3158] = "How unfortunate! The last storm actually damaged the hull of my wonderful ship. However, if you bring me back 15698758² Ash planks and 100 Kamas, I\'ll be able to fix it and take you there for free. I\'m a very generous person... Don\'t be silly! I\'m kidding... There\'s no way I\'m taking a ninny like you on my boat!";
D.q[1866] = "Hum, I believe you. You don\'t look like you could do much anyway.";
D.q[2227] = "Hum... I think I\'ll be able to help you. I\'m going to use a potion to stiffen the string. Then, you\'ll see how precise your bow will be. Stay here, I\'ll do that right now.";
D.q[2494] = "Hum? Ask Manganeze! I\'m busy!";
D.q[6518] = "Salutations, my Brakmarian comrade. Don\'t, whatever you do, tell Oto that I\'m playing during my free time, otherwise he\'ll punish me for not doing so during work hours.";
D.q[2166] = "Humm? Ah, *koff koff*, I\'m as sick as a Bow Wow. I can\'t work today. I JUST CAN\'T!!! Look at my skin. I never get spots. I can\'t leave the house.";
D.q[2974] = "I advise you destroy this item straight away! You don\'t want to be caught with a Dofawa by the mercenaries of Astrub, believe me... The best thing for you to do would be to get some information about the governing laws of our regions. This way you won\'t put your life at stake unnecessarily. Go to the jail in Astrub, mercenaries will tell you more about Dofus and Pandala.";
D.q[3036] = "I also have kinky scrolls! But I don\'t think that will interest a pure young warrior like you! I also have a glossary, the Dofusus Glossary, to be exact. It\'s very useful if you\'re having trouble understanding some of this warrior jargon.";
D.q[6376] = "Yuuuuummm. Very good this dish is. Some Rasputin Cake you have added? Undoubtedly a great chef you are.";
D.q[567] = "I\'m Gropinson Cruaule, didn\'t I tell you already? I\'ve been a tourist here for 50 years now, hahaha. The travel agency promised me a one-way ticket to heaven. They didn\'t lie but I still have a few years before I get there... hahaha!";
D.q[333] = "I\'m weally scattewbwained, the cowwidow leading to the secwet hall is unpassable since it collapsed.\nSevewal wobots awe cleawing the way.\nUnless you tuwn wight in the passage behind me, you\'ll awwive in the wabbit quawtew of the special fowces. But they will cewtainly attack you, they awe a bit wough and weady.";
D.q[2634] = "I beg your pardon?";
D.q[697] = "I can exchange you a stock of 100 Standard Strings for 100 units of Flax.";
D.q[2790] = "I bet you wanna go to the evil Forest!";
